Program: Discovery
Title: The Future of the Forests - Climate Change
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxn8
Last Broadcast Date: 13 July 2000
Examination of what climate change will mean for the world's forests. Will the once lush rainforests become dry savannah as our planet's temperature rises. Global warming, a rise of about 3 degrees celsius, will have implications for the way and rate at which plants grow.